[SN]TITLE[SN]
London shares see mixed opening

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
(Open): The FTSE 100 had a mixed opening as investors digested a number of corporate results and updates.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The benchmark FTSE 100 index was up 6.15 points at 6,933.73, with Imperial Tobacco the top riser on the index.
Shares in the tobacco firm rose 2.4% after it said it was on track to meet its financial targets, despite underlying half-year sales dropping 5%.
Sainsbury's shares were down 1.4% after the supermarket chain reported its first full-year loss for 10 years.
The UK's third-largest supermarket chain reported a Â£72m loss in the year to March, after being hit by several one-off costs, including a write-down in the value of some of its stores.
In the FTSE 250, shares in Superdry owner Supergroup rose 3.7% after it reported strong fourth-quarter sales.
The fashion chain reported an 11.6% rise in like-for-like sales for the 15 weeks to 25 April, and said it was on track to hit full-year targets.
